cs.NA, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the analysis of numerical errors in computer programs, which is a topic in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach to analysis that characterizes the input/output behavior of code fragments, which is related to program analysis and verification, and thus cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are also likely sub-categories. The paper deals with loops and branches in programs, which are topics in formal methods and logic, and thus cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to error propagation that separates the propagation of existing errors from the roundoff or truncation errors committed during the computation, which is related to control theory and system dynamics, and thus cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category.
